The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
 Tuesday, August 05, 2003 				 Doctors robbed
																								Calcutta, Aug. 4: A gang of three raided the flat of a doctor couple on Bampass Road in Tollygunge tonight and decamped with Rs 15,000 and gold jewellery, says a staff reporter.																								Police said the trio entered the flat of Dr Sailen Addi and Dr Manjulika Addi posing as patients. Manjulika, who is attached to the School of Tropical Medicine, was alone then. The miscreants disconnected telephone lines and held choppers on her head while asking for the keys to the almirah. She screamed for help after the goons left the flat.
